    "bio_summary": "Olivia Isabel Rodrigo (born February 20, 2003 in Murrieta, CA, USA) is an American singer-songwriter and actress. She began her career as a child, appearing in commercials and the direct-to-video film \"An American Girl: Grace Stirs Up Success\" (2015). She gained recognition for her leading roles in the Disney Channel series \"Bizaardvark\" (2016–2019) and the Disney+ series \"High School Musical: The Musical: The Series\" (2019–2022).\n\nRodrigo signed with Geffen Records and released her 2021 single \"Drivers License\"",
    "bio_content": "Olivia Isabel Rodrigo (born February 20, 2003 in Murrieta, CA, USA) is an American singer-songwriter and actress. She began her career as a child, appearing in commercials and the direct-to-video film \"An American Girl: Grace Stirs Up Success\" (2015). She gained recognition for her leading roles in the Disney Channel series \"Bizaardvark\" (2016–2019) and the Disney+ series \"High School Musical: The Musical: The Series\" (2019–2022).\n\nRodrigo signed with Geffen Records and released her 2021 single \"Drivers License\", which reached number one on the US Billboard Hot 100 for eight consecutive weeks. Her debut studio album, \"Sour\" (2021), included the singles \"Good 4 U\", \"Deja Vu\", \"Traitor\", and \"Brutal\". A documentary, \"Olivia Rodrigo: Driving Home 2 U\", which explores the making of \"Sour\", was released in 2022. In 2023, she released her second studio album, \"Guts\", which featured the singles \"Vampire\", \"Bad Idea Right?\", and \"Get Him Back!\".\n\nRodrigo has achieved three Billboard Hot 100 number-one singles, two US Billboard 200 number-one albums, and multiple songs with multi-platinum certifications from the Recording Industry Association of America (RIAA). She has received awards including three Grammy Awards, four MTV Video Music Awards, and seven Billboard Music Awards. She was named Time's Entertainer of the Year in 2021, Billboard's Woman of the Year in 2022, and ASCAP's Pop Music Songwriter of the Year in 2022 and 2024.\n\nStudio albums\nSour (2021)\nGuts (2023) <a href=\"https://www.last.fm/music/Olivia+Rodrigo\">Read more on Last.fm</a>. User-contributed text is available under the Creative Commons By-SA License; additional terms may apply.",
